@'\"! tbl|eqn | mmdoc
'\"macro stdmacro
.ds Vn Version 1.2
.ds Dt 10 Nov 1998
.ds Re Release 1.0
.ds Dp Apr 04 17:39
.ds Dm  Apr  4  200
.ds Xs 40062 6 fglclearcolor.gl
.TH FGLCLEARCOLOR 
.SH NAME
.B "fglClearColor
\- specify clear values for the color buffers

.SH FORTRAN SPECIFICATION
SUBROUTINE \f3fglClearColor\fP(
REAL*4 \fIred\fP,
.nf
.ta \w'\f3SUBROUTINE \fPfglClearColor( 'u
	REAL*4 \fIgreen\fP,
	REAL*4 \fIblue\fP,
	REAL*4 \fIalpha\fP )
.fi

.SH PARAMETERS
.TP \w'\f2red\fP\ \f2green\fP\ \f2blue\fP\ \f2alpha\fP\ \ 'u 
\f2red\fP, \f2green\fP, \f2blue\fP, \f2alpha\fP
Specify the red, green, blue, and alpha values used when the
color buffers are cleared.
The initial values are all 0.
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f3fglClearColor\fP specifies the red,
green,
blue,
and alpha values used by \f3fglClear\fP to clear the color buffers.
Values specified by \f3fglClearColor\fP are clamped to the range [0,\ 1].
.SH ERRORS
\f3GL_INVALID_OPERATION\fP is generated if \f3fglClearColor\fP
is executed between the execution of \f3fglBegin\fP
and the corresponding execution of \f3fglEnd\fP.
.SH ASSOCIATED GETS
\f3fglGet\fP with argument \f3GL_COLOR_CLEAR_VALUE\fP
.SH SEE ALSO
\f3fglClear\fP
@


